sentences.sContent: Alternatively, the dead could have been killed on the spot in "the swampy valley environment", the paper concludes.
sentences.sContent_eng: Alternatively, the dead could have been killed on the spot in "the swampy valley environment", the paper concludes.
sentences.sCn: 另一种可能是，这些死者是在有“沼泽河谷环境”的地点被杀害的——论文总结道。

sentences.sContent: On rare clearings in this swampy hell a few Finno-Ugric tribes eventually appeared and left many burial mounts behind, with some of them still belowground because of impassibility of the swamp.
sentences.sContent_eng: On rare clearings in this swampy hell a few Finno-Ugric tribes eventually appeared and left many burial mounts behind, with some of them still belowground because of impassibility of the swamp.
sentences.sCn: 在这难得如此空旷的沼泽地狱里，几个芬兰乌戈尔部落终于出现了，身后留下了许多坟墓，其中有些还是地下，因为的沼泽是那么不近人情。

synos.tran: [地理][水文]沼泽的；湿地的；沼泽多的；松软的

remMethod.val: swamp(沼泽) + y(形容词后缀) → 沼泽(多)的， 湿地的

words.tran: 下沉；陷入沼泽；陷入困境；不知所措（过去式swamped，过去分词swamped，现在分词swamping，第三人称单数swamps，名词swampiness，形容词swampy）
使陷于沼泽；使沉没；使陷入困境
